HEADWORD: Polyptoton
<hw>Pol`yp*to"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/ having, or being in, many cases; <grk>poly`s</grk> many + <?/
case.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure by which a word is
repeated in different forms, cases, numbers, genders, etc., as in
Tennyson's line, -- ⟦ldquo⟧My own heart's heart, and ownest own,
farewell.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polypus</ent>⟦br⟧
